        <h1>LeetCode 693: Binary Number with Alternating Bits (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a positive integer, check whether it has alternating bits: namely, if two adjacent bits will
                always have different values. Return true if the number has alternating bits, otherwise return false.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: n = 5<br>
                Output: true<br>
                Explanation: The binary representation of 5 is 101, which has alternating bits (1-0-1).
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool hasAlternatingBits(int num) {
        unsigned int temp = num ^ (num &gt;&gt; 1);
        // check if temp is of form 111... (power of 2 minus 1)
        return (temp &amp; (temp + 1)) == 0;
    }
};</code></pre>
